<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="27" type="holotype">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="27">Holotype.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="27">
MEXICO, Veracruz State, Alto Lucero Co., 12 km SW Palma Sola (road Veracruz-Nautla) 25 June 2015, Montoya 5190 (XAL). Ectomycorrhizal, under 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Quercus oleoides" order="Fagales" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="oleoides">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">Quercus oleoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="27" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="27">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="27">
<taxonomicName class="Agaricomycetes" family="Russulaceae" genus="Lactifluus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Lactifluus lorenae" order="Russulales" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="lorenae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">Lactifluus lorenae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is clearly distinguished by white basidiomes, staining orange-brown, latex staining white paper yellow, odour somewhat chlorine-like, basidiospores broadly ellipsoid, pleuromacrocystidia 40-53 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
7-9 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
and pileipellis a hyphoepithelium with a gelatinzied hyphoid layer, 30-60 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
wide.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="27" type="gene sequences ex-holotype">
